//Anterior cruciate ligament (ACL)


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 - Ligaments, joint capsule & menisci of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Anterior cruciate ligament (ACL)' from the Finding dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Injury, acute' radio button is enabled
And 'Injury, chronic' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Injury, acute' radio button
Then 'Total rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Popliteus tendon rupture' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Total rupture' radio button
Then 'Signal increase T2w' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Contusion/Bone Marrow Edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fracture' checkbox is enabled
And 'Anterior tibial subluxation > 5mm' checkbox is enabled
And 'Buckling of the PCL' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Contusion/Bone Marrow Edema' checkbox
Then 'Anterolateral femur condyle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Posterolat. tibia plateau' checkbox is enabled
And 'Contrecoup: posteromedial tibial plateau' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Fracture' checkbox
Then 'Anterolateral femur condyle (AO 33)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Posterolat. tibia plateau' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tibial eminence (AO 41A1.3)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Proximal Fibula (AO 4F1)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lat. tibial plateau (AO 41A1-1)' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Proximal Fibula (AO 4F1)' checkbox
Then 'Arcuate sign' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Arcuate sign' checkbox
Then 'Avulsion fibula' checkbox is enabled
And 'Avulsion of the posterolateral capsule' checkbox is enabled
And 'Rupture of the posterior cruciate ligament' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Lat. tibial plateau (AO 41A1-1)' checkbox
Then 'Segond fracture' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Segond fracture' checkbox
Then 'Tibial avulsion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Rupture anterior cruciate ligament' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Partial rupture' radio button
Then 'Anteromedial bundle' radio button is enabled
And 'Posterolateral bundle' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Injury, chronic' radio button
Then 'ACL, without surgery' radio button is enabled
And 'ACL graft' radio button is enabled

When I select 'ACL, without surgery' radio button
Then 'Signal increase in T2w' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Synovialization' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ganglion cyst' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Ganglion cyst' checkbox
Then 'Max. dimension in mm' input field is enabled

When I select 'ACL graft' radio button
Then 'Graft failure' radio button is enabled
And 'Graft re-rupture' radio button is enabled
And '"Tunnel" cyst' checkbox is enabled
When I select '"Tunnel" cyst' checkbox
Then 'Tibial' checkbox is enabled
And '"Femoral' checkbox is enabled
